====Usage notes====
This note is discussed on the talk page.
*Beginning in the 1950s, the term '''communism''' was used to describe something negative. This usage is very similar to the way the word ''[[gay]]'' is used. This practice is derived from the fact that people, during the [[Wikipedia:Red Scare|Red Scare]], accused those they disliked of being communists for ludicrous reasons. For example, when a test is difficult or unfair, one can say, "That's communism." This colloquial usage is restricted primarily to [[American English]].

